1
00:00:01,209 --> 00:00:05,130
(eerie music plays)

2
00:00:07,257 --> 00:00:09,843
(wind howling)

3
00:00:14,389 --> 00:00:16,725
(humming)

4
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:18,226
Mm-hmm.

5
00:00:18,309 --> 00:00:20,562
Hello, I’d like to vote
for president, governor,

6
00:00:20,645 --> 00:00:21,896
and anything that will take
money away

7
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:23,481
from our parks and libraries.

8
00:00:23,565 --> 00:00:25,942
Eh, use machine
number three.

9
00:00:26,026 --> 00:00:27,152
(humming)

10
00:00:27,235 --> 00:00:28,778
(grunts)

11
00:00:28,862 --> 00:00:29,821
Oh!

12
00:00:29,904 --> 00:00:32,073
I can’t fit in the booth!

13
00:00:32,157 --> 00:00:33,783
Use the double-wide.

14
00:00:38,079 --> 00:00:39,247
Ooh!

15
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:42,125
One of those <i>electronic</i>
voting dealies.

16
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:44,544
<i>COMPUTER VOICE:</i>
<i>One vote for McCain. Thank you.</i>

17
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:45,754
(chuckles)

18
00:00:45,837 --> 00:00:47,881
No, I want to vote for Obama.

19
00:00:47,964 --> 00:00:49,424
<i>Two votes for McCain.</i>

20
00:00:49,507 --> 00:00:50,508
Huh?!

21
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:52,135
Come on. It’s time for a change.

22
00:00:52,218 --> 00:00:54,179
<i>Three votes for McCain.</i>

23
00:00:54,262 --> 00:00:55,638
No! No! No!

24
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:57,724
<i>Six votes for President McCain.</i>

25
00:00:57,807 --> 00:01:00,351
Hey, I only meant one
of those votes for McCain.

26
00:01:00,435 --> 00:01:03,146
(gasps)
This machine is rigged.

27
00:01:03,229 --> 00:01:04,939
(whirring)

28
00:01:05,023 --> 00:01:08,735
Must... tell.. President McCain.

29
00:01:08,818 --> 00:01:09,986
(shrieks)
This doesn’t happen in America.

30
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:12,864
Maybe Ohio, but not in America!

31
00:01:12,947 --> 00:01:15,116
(screaming)

32
00:01:19,746 --> 00:01:21,414
("Hail to the Chief" plays)

33
00:01:34,219 --> 00:01:37,514
(dramatic music plays)

34
00:01:46,564 --> 00:01:47,440
Okay...

35
00:01:47,524 --> 00:01:52,070
all I need is a Christmas gift
for Lisa.

36
00:01:52,153 --> 00:01:53,571
I don’t have time
to read all that.

37
00:01:53,655 --> 00:01:55,240
(humming)

38
00:01:55,323 --> 00:01:56,241
Hmm?

39
00:01:56,324 --> 00:01:59,619
Montreal Expos jersey.

40
00:01:59,702 --> 00:02:01,162
Somber String.

41
00:02:01,246 --> 00:02:03,498
Jacks, no ball.

42
00:02:03,581 --> 00:02:05,416
And a Slunky.

43
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,793
Oh, I wouldn’t give these
to my worst enemy,

44
00:02:06,876 --> 00:02:08,419
which happens to be Lisa.

45
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:10,213
(whirrs, clicks)

46
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:12,298
Girls don’t like trucks.

47
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:13,716
Come back when you’re
something else.

48
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,511
(whirring)

49
00:02:16,594 --> 00:02:17,595
-(honks)
-(gasps)

50
00:02:17,679 --> 00:02:19,264
Perfect!

51
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:22,809
Merry Christmas, Dad.

52
00:02:22,892 --> 00:02:25,812
We bought you three
more minutes of oxygen.

53
00:02:25,895 --> 00:02:27,105
Oh, thank you, son!

54
00:02:27,188 --> 00:02:28,815
Can I play with it outside?

55
00:02:28,898 --> 00:02:29,858
Can I?! Can I?!

56
00:02:29,941 --> 00:02:31,985
(chuckles)
Sure.

57
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:33,027
(laughs)

58
00:02:33,111 --> 00:02:34,487
(breathing rapidly)

59
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:36,114
(laughing)

60
00:02:40,577 --> 00:02:42,120
Hmm?

61
00:02:42,203 --> 00:02:45,498
Hey, Lis, I think I see one
with your name on it.

62
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:47,458
I don’t know how you could top
last year’s gift--

63
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:49,502
a box of your burps.

64
00:02:49,586 --> 00:02:51,462
Yeah. Here’s your
stocking stuffer.

65
00:02:51,546 --> 00:02:52,839
(belches loudly)

66
00:02:55,508 --> 00:02:58,845
Wow! A Malibu Stacey
convertible!

67
00:02:58,928 --> 00:03:02,265
Oh, Bart, an actual present.

68
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:04,350
(whirrs)

69
00:03:06,603 --> 00:03:07,520
(zapping)

70
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:08,605
(crackling)

71
00:03:08,688 --> 00:03:10,356
(pops)

72
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:12,192
(whirs)

73
00:03:12,275 --> 00:03:15,111
That’s right, Maggie.
It’s a car.

74
00:03:17,197 --> 00:03:18,740
(whirrs)

75
00:03:22,827 --> 00:03:24,245
(whirs)

76
00:03:26,998 --> 00:03:30,752
<i>MALIBU STACEY:</i>
<i>Let’s go to the... (grunting)</i>

77
00:03:30,835 --> 00:03:34,047
(zapping)

78
00:03:34,130 --> 00:03:36,633
(deep, heroic voice):
Pos-i-bots, transform!

79
00:03:38,509 --> 00:03:39,969
Snooze!

80
00:03:42,263 --> 00:03:43,348
Threeway!

81
00:03:43,431 --> 00:03:44,682
(clicks three times)

82
00:03:46,768 --> 00:03:48,061
(deep male voice):
Melody!

83
00:03:48,144 --> 00:03:49,437
(moans)

84
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,855
(whirring)

85
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:53,733
What?

86
00:03:53,816 --> 00:03:54,943
(groans)

87
00:03:55,026 --> 00:03:56,402
(clicks and whirs)

88
00:03:56,486 --> 00:03:58,196
