We’re missing Sex-Toy.

89
00:03:58,279 --> 00:04:00,698
(soft, jazzy music plays)

90
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:01,950
Where have you been?

91
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:04,869
(chuckles)
Where haven’t I been?

92
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:09,165
(whirring, clicking)

93
00:04:09,249 --> 00:04:10,792
Hmm. Is there
something different

94
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:12,377
about the kitchen?

95
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:13,586
ALL: No.

96
00:04:14,963 --> 00:04:16,631
(whirs, clicks)

97
00:04:16,714 --> 00:04:20,176
Well, the toaster’s never lied
to me before.

98
00:04:21,844 --> 00:04:23,471
Hep, two, three, four...

99
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:24,681
Nice planet.

100
00:04:24,764 --> 00:04:26,266
(humming)

101
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:31,187
-(clanking)
-HOMER: Whoa!

102
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:32,814
(screams)

103
00:04:32,897 --> 00:04:35,441
(whirs)

104
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:36,818
(grunts)

105
00:04:36,901 --> 00:04:38,403
(mechanical, droning voice)
Pos-i-bot, engage.

106
00:04:38,486 --> 00:04:40,822
Battle commencing
in ten, nine, eight...

107
00:04:40,905 --> 00:04:41,823
Hey!

108
00:04:41,906 --> 00:04:44,242
(clanking, whirring)

109
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:46,202
Hey, Homer.
How was your Christmas?

110
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:48,204
It was okay.
I got <i>Seinfeld, </i>Season 7.

111
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:53,668
Finally a boxing day
that lives up to its name.

112
00:04:53,751 --> 00:04:55,753
Lisa! What’s happening?!

113
00:04:55,837 --> 00:04:57,422
Well, if I had
to guess,

114
00:04:57,505 --> 00:04:59,465
I’d say that two
alien robot races,

115
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:01,592
who’ve been battling
for centuries, have chosen

116
00:05:01,676 --> 00:05:04,429
our planet as a site for their
ultimate confrontation.

117
00:05:04,512 --> 00:05:06,306
It is a good planet
to settle things on.

118
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:10,935
(tires screech)

119
00:05:11,019 --> 00:05:13,771
(clanking)

120
00:05:16,065 --> 00:05:18,109
-(whirring)
-(gasps)

121
00:05:18,192 --> 00:05:19,944
Stop it! Stop it!

122
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:22,697
Look, you have made
the nacho machine cry.

123
00:05:24,949 --> 00:05:27,410
(whirring)

124
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:28,953
Cool!

125
00:05:30,038 --> 00:05:32,498
Carnage Destructicus,

126
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:35,293
the moment has arrived:
our final battle.

127
00:05:35,376 --> 00:05:37,045
(clanking, whirring)

128
00:05:37,128 --> 00:05:40,131
<i>Your </i>final battle,
Bestimus Mucho!

129
00:05:42,383 --> 00:05:43,634
Stop it!

130
00:05:43,718 --> 00:05:45,303
Just because you’re mad
at each other,

131
00:05:45,386 --> 00:05:47,513
doesn’t mean you have
to destroy our town.

132
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:48,723
That does not compute.

133
00:05:48,806 --> 00:05:49,891
Really?!

134
00:05:49,974 --> 00:05:51,851
It computes a little.

135
00:05:51,934 --> 00:05:54,645
What’s this whole intergalactic
tiff about anyway?

136
00:05:54,729 --> 00:05:57,690
You know I, I...
I don’t remember.

137
00:05:57,774 --> 00:05:59,025
Neither do I.

138
00:05:59,108 --> 00:06:02,779
Hmm. Maybe the non-transforma
thing is right.

139
00:06:02,862 --> 00:06:04,614
Thank you,
human grandmother,

140
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:06,407
for pointing out
that it is futile to fight

141
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:07,825
if we do not know why.

142
00:06:07,909 --> 00:06:09,952
And now that we are
not fighting each other,

143
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,537
we can team up

144
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:13,998
to enslave your planet.

145
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:15,750
That’s great!

146
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:16,876
Because working together,
you can...

147
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:18,169
Oh...

148
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:21,172
(yelling)

149
00:06:21,255 --> 00:06:25,301
Okay, who’s the idiot who
taught them what foosball was?

150
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:26,761
I thought
they might enjoy it.

151
00:06:26,844 --> 00:06:27,929
(yelling)

152
00:06:33,184 --> 00:06:36,187
( <i>Mad Men </i>theme paying)

153
00:06:46,823 --> 00:06:50,243
♪ ♪

154
00:07:00,128 --> 00:07:02,171
♪ ♪

155
00:07:12,974 --> 00:07:15,476
(children giggling)

156
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:19,230
Okay, Maggie, we’ll be back
in three hours.

157
00:07:19,313 --> 00:07:22,233
Or longer if something
happens to us.

158
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:27,113
Maybe we shouldn’t
do this.

159
00:07:27,196 --> 00:07:28,656
She doesn’t know
anyone here.

160
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:31,951
Look, sweetie,
there’s a familiar face--

161
00:07:32,034 --> 00:07:33,786
Krusty!

162
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:36,122
(Maggie giggling)

163
00:07:46,174 --> 00:07:48,050
Hey, hey, kids!

164
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,928
Your old pal Krusty’s gonna
teach you five new words:

165
00:07:51,012 --> 00:07:53,473
unlicensed use of my image.

166
00:07:56,642 --> 00:07:57,727
All right, boys.

167
00:07:57,810 --> 00:08:00,688
See those Krustys
nobody paid me for?

168
00:08:00,771 --> 00:08:02,607
Sandblast them!

169
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,947
Entertain the troops?

170
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:11,491
No way!

171
00:08:11,574 --> 00:08:13,284
What have <i>they</i>
ever done for me?!

172
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:15,953
Krusty, you made
my daughter cry!

173
00:08:16,037 --> 00:08:18,372
Hey, my intellectual property
rights were being infringed.

174
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:20,082
Do you know
how that feels?

175
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:21,751
Do ya?! Huh?! Do ya?!

176
00:08:21,834 --> 00:08:22,752
(grunts)

177
00:08:22,835 --> 00:08:24,420
(yelling)

178
00:08:28,966 --> 00:08:30,718
(screaming)

179
00:08:38,768 --> 00:08:42,188
One, two, three.

180
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:44,524
Oh! It’s no use.

181
00:08:47,151 --> 00:08:48,611
(doorbell rings)

182
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:52,740
Mr. Simpson, you have
quite a talent

183
00:08:52,823 --> 00:08:55,076
for killing celebrities.

184
00:08:55,159 --> 00:08:56,285
(chuckling modestly):
Well...

185
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:58,287
I’m no drunk driving.

186
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:01,666
I’d like to introduce you
to some stereotypical ad men.

187
00:09:01,749 --> 00:09:03,626
Simpson, we got a swell
little notion for you.

188
00:09:03,709 --> 00:09:06,462
Did you know you can put
a dead celebrity in a commercial

189
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:08,130
and you don’t have
to pay them a thing?

190
00:09:12,009 --> 00:09:15,555
♪ ♪

191
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:22,728
Oh, my God, you finally did it.

192
00:09:22,812 --> 00:09:24,814
You mixed Buzz Cola

193
00:09:24,897 --> 00:09:28,109
