259
00:12:18,779 --> 00:12:19,530
-(gasps)
-Huh?

260
00:12:19,613 --> 00:12:22,074
(rumbling)

261
00:12:22,158 --> 00:12:23,451
(gunfire)

262
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:25,119
(people screaming)

263
00:12:28,622 --> 00:12:31,250
G-g-g-golda Meir!

264
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,961
("Hava Nagila" playing)

265
00:12:34,044 --> 00:12:34,879
(sighs)

266
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:37,298
Ah, you ripped me off. See?

267
00:12:37,381 --> 00:12:39,133
No, I didn’t. See!

268
00:12:39,216 --> 00:12:41,719
You’re gonna pay
for what you done. See!

269
00:12:41,802 --> 00:12:43,137
(groans)

270
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:46,807
I always thought I’d die
of hepatitis... C.

271
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:48,809
(groans)

272
00:12:48,893 --> 00:12:50,394
Rip Taylor?

273
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:51,812
You’re not even dead!

274
00:12:51,896 --> 00:12:53,606
Someone needs to check
my apartment.

275
00:12:53,689 --> 00:12:54,815
(laughs)

276
00:12:54,899 --> 00:12:57,526
(humming)

277
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:00,488
(gasps)

278
00:13:00,571 --> 00:13:02,031
Let’s get him!

279
00:13:02,114 --> 00:13:05,451
Little Sister, is that
moustache comin’ or goin’?

280
00:13:05,534 --> 00:13:06,994
Well, your wife likes it.

281
00:13:08,788 --> 00:13:10,664
(laughing)

282
00:13:10,748 --> 00:13:13,042
You’re all right,
Goofy Grape.

283
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:14,335
People, please.

284
00:13:14,418 --> 00:13:15,586
(cocks gun)
We’re here to kill this jerk.

285
00:13:15,669 --> 00:13:17,755
Before you kill me,
I gotta know...

286
00:13:17,838 --> 00:13:20,007
what is the one true religion?

287
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:22,760
It’s a mix of voodoo
and Methodist.

288
00:13:24,553 --> 00:13:25,638
(Homer grunts)

289
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:27,056
(laughs)

290
00:13:27,139 --> 00:13:29,725
Shouldn’t have left the key
under the mat, suckers!

291
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:31,727
So what do you do
for fun around here?

292
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:33,687
Well, tonight we’ve got
a poker tournament

293
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:34,980
at the rec center.

294
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:36,398
Ooh!

295
00:13:36,482 --> 00:13:38,526
After you, Mr. Pennyface.

296
00:13:38,609 --> 00:13:39,902
Is your wife up here?

297
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:41,362
(chuckles)

298
00:13:41,445 --> 00:13:43,948
Well, uh, we have
an understanding.

299
00:13:44,031 --> 00:13:46,158
Mmm.

300
00:13:49,036 --> 00:13:52,581
( <i>Peanuts </i>theme song playing)

301
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:22,111
(yawning)

302
00:14:30,786 --> 00:14:32,621
Phew!

303
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,123
Good grief.

304
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:37,793
I like your witch
costume, Lisa.

305
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:40,629
I’m not a witch.
I’m a Wiccan.

306
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:42,506
Why is it when a woman is
confident and powerful,

307
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:43,716
they call her a witch?

308
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:44,925
(trombone playing)

309
00:14:45,009 --> 00:14:46,010
What did you say, Mom?

310
00:14:46,093 --> 00:14:47,011
Nothing.

311
00:14:47,094 --> 00:14:48,804
I’m practicing
my trombone.

312
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:50,431
♪ ♪

313
00:14:50,514 --> 00:14:51,724
So, what are you wearing

314
00:14:51,807 --> 00:14:53,517
to the Halloween party,
Milhouse?

315
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:55,102
I’m not going
to the party.

316
00:14:55,185 --> 00:14:56,687
I’m going to the
pumpkin patch

317
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:59,690
to wait for the
Grand Pumpkin!

318
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:01,275
♪ ♪

319
00:15:01,358 --> 00:15:03,527
That means
"you kids have fun"!

320
00:15:03,611 --> 00:15:06,030
What’s the Grand Pumpkin?

321
00:15:06,113 --> 00:15:07,489
Every Halloween,

322
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:09,325
the Grand Pumpkin visits

323
00:15:09,408 --> 00:15:11,744
all the pumpkin patches
in the world

324
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:14,747
and brings candy to kids
who truly believe!

325
00:15:14,830 --> 00:15:16,916
Milhouse, for the
last time,

326
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,918
I made that up
to mess with you.

327
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:20,920
The Grand Pumpkin
isn’t real!

328
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:23,589
I appreciate you
testing my faith, Bart,

329
00:15:23,672 --> 00:15:25,591
but it’s not necessary.

330
00:15:25,674 --> 00:15:27,968
I believe in the Grand Pumpkin,
almighty gourd,

331
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:29,970
who was crustified
over Pontius Pie-plate,

332
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:31,597
and ascended into oven.

333
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:34,350
He will come again to judge
the filling and the bread...

334
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:37,353
Sigh.

335
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:42,232
(gasps)
You’ve all come

336
00:15:42,316 --> 00:15:44,234
to wait for the
Grand Pumpkin with me!

337
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:46,403
Who wants to sing
pumpkin carols?

338
00:15:46,487 --> 00:15:48,197
I’ve got a pumpkin
carol for you.

339
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:49,615
(clears throat)

340
00:15:49,698 --> 00:15:51,784
♪ You are such
a stupid moron ♪

341
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:53,619
♪ It makes people
want to punch you ♪

342
00:15:53,702 --> 00:15:56,163
♪ The Grand Pumpkin’s
superga-ay ♪

343
00:15:56,246 --> 00:15:58,123
♪ Punch, punch, punch,
punch, wedgie! ♪

344
00:15:58,207 --> 00:15:59,959
(groans)

345
00:16:00,042 --> 00:16:01,293
(laughing)

346
00:16:01,377 --> 00:16:03,295
Your god is wrong!

347
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:04,630
Let’s get
to the Halloween party.

348
00:16:04,713 --> 00:16:06,048
I want to hit
the apple tank

349
00:16:06,131 --> 00:16:07,591
before all the Granny
Smiths are bobbed out.

350
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:09,051
Lis, you comin’?

351
00:16:09,134 --> 00:16:10,844
Eh, I think I’ll stay
with Milhouse.

352
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:13,055
His glasses fog up
when he cries.

353
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:14,807
DOLPH:
More Granny Smiths
for me.

354
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:24,149
Lisa, Lisa, wake up!

355
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:25,859
-He’s here!
-What?

356
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:27,528
The Grand Pumpkin is here?!

357
00:16:27,611 --> 00:16:30,739
No. I’m rehearsing what I’m
gonna say when he shows up.

358
00:16:30,823 --> 00:16:32,282
He’s here! He’s here!

359
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:34,201
He is here!

360
00:16:34,284 --> 00:16:36,620
♪ ♪

361
00:16:36,704 --> 00:16:39,665
You owe me restitution!

362
00:16:39,748 --> 00:16:42,209
If he sees us fighting,
he might not come.

363
00:16:42,292 --> 00:16:44,461
(groans)

364
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:46,880
Grand Pumpkin,

365
00:16:46,964 --> 00:16:48,632
I know you’re real.

366
00:16:48,716 --> 00:16:50,592
Why won’t you show yourself?!

367
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:52,678
(sobbing):
Why?

368
00:16:52,761 --> 00:16:54,972
(sobbing)

369
00:16:57,808 --> 00:16:59,601
Whoa!

370
00:17:02,730 --> 00:17:05,566
Happy Halloween!

371
00:17:05,649 --> 00:17:07,860
The Grand Pumpkin!

372
00:17:07,943 --> 00:17:10,154
You <i>are </i>real!

373
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:12,448
That’s right, Milhouse.

374
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:15,909
Your childlike belief
has brought me to life!

375
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:17,953
I knew you’d come!

376
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:21,206
I even baked you a loaf
of homemade pumpkin bread!

377
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:22,708
Oh, how delightful--

378
00:17:22,791 --> 00:17:25,461
bread made especially
for pumpkins.

379
00:17:25,544 --> 00:17:27,504
(munching)

380
00:17:27,588 --> 00:17:29,465
-Mm-hmm.
-Actually,

381
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:30,799
it’s made <i>from </i>pumpkins.

382
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:32,593
Wha...?!

383
00:17:32,676 --> 00:17:35,345
(vomiting)

384
00:17:35,429 --> 00:17:36,764
Uh-oh.

385
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:39,475
Revenge!

386
00:17:39,558 --> 00:17:41,268
(screams)

387
00:17:41,351 --> 00:17:43,270
(panting)

388
00:17:43,353 --> 00:17:45,022
(chuckles)

389
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:46,523
I’m gonna give you
crossed eyes

390
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:47,858
like you might see
on an idiot,

391
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:50,152
a stupid triangle nose,

392
00:17:50,235 --> 00:17:51,570
and a big mouth

393
00:17:51,653 --> 00:17:53,739
full of the ugliest shaped
teeth there are--

394
00:17:53,822 --> 00:17:55,365
square.

395
00:17:55,449 --> 00:17:58,077
And I’m gonna make
your friends watch.

396
00:18:02,247 --> 00:18:05,209
(screaming):
No!

397
00:18:05,292 --> 00:18:06,293
(whimpering)

398
00:18:08,504 --> 00:18:10,089
Ladies.

399
00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:12,132
Stupid.

400
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:13,884
(airplane whirring)

401
00:18:16,386 --> 00:18:18,055
♪ ♪

402
00:18:21,642 --> 00:18:23,977
Everybody, listen!

403
00:18:24,061 --> 00:18:25,521
The Grand Pumpkin is real!

404
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:26,355
Hey!

405
00:18:26,438 --> 00:18:28,774
-No hard-soled shoes!
-(thud)

406
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:31,151
(kids screaming)

407
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:33,153
Oh, God!

408
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:34,696
Everywhere I look--

409
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:37,491
pumpkin atrocities!

410
00:18:37,574 --> 00:18:39,910
Care for a pumpkin seed?

411
00:18:39,993 --> 00:18:40,911
-(sizzling)
-(gasps)

412
00:18:40,994 --> 00:18:43,288
You roast the unborn?

413
00:18:43,372 --> 00:18:45,124
(screams)

414
00:18:45,207 --> 00:18:47,751
(grunting)

415
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:50,087
Touch me
and I’ll cut your friend!

416
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:51,505
What do I care?

417
00:18:51,588 --> 00:18:53,006
That’s a yellow pumpkin.

418
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:55,175
(gasps)
You’re a racist!

419
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:56,760
All pumpkins are racist.

420
00:18:56,844 --> 00:18:58,345
The difference is I admit it!

421
00:18:58,428 --> 00:18:59,972
(grunts)

422
00:19:00,055 --> 00:19:02,015
I’d rather die
than hate!

423
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:03,892
This is all my fault!

424
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:06,019
The Grand Pumpkin said
my childlike belief

425
00:19:06,103 --> 00:19:08,063
was what made him
come to life!

426
00:19:08,147 --> 00:19:09,648
Belief, eh?

427
00:19:09,731 --> 00:19:11,441
Hmm.

428
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:13,527
Say, Milhouse, have
you by any chance

429
00:19:13,610 --> 00:19:15,571
ever heard of
"Tom Turkey"?

430
00:19:15,654 --> 00:19:18,323
No. Who is he
and what’s his origin story?

431
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:19,491
Um...

432
00:19:19,575 --> 00:19:21,493
well, Tom is a magical turkey

433
00:19:21,577 --> 00:19:22,995
who gave the pilgrims
the technology

434
00:19:23,078 --> 00:19:24,288
to put buckles on their hats.

435
00:19:24,371 --> 00:19:26,206
Now he appears
every Thanksgiving

436
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:27,958
to children
who believe.

437
00:19:28,041 --> 00:19:29,543
Sounds plausible.

438
00:19:29,626 --> 00:19:31,545
Tom Turkey, help me.

439
00:19:31,628 --> 00:19:33,672
I believe in you.

440
00:19:33,755 --> 00:19:36,633
Are you looking for a particular
part of my brain or...

441
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:41,430
Halt, yon pumperkin

442
00:19:41,513 --> 00:19:43,932
most succulent and plump!

443
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:46,602
I be Tom Turkey!

444
00:19:46,685 --> 00:19:49,229
A giant talking turkey?

445
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:51,106
Preposterous!

446
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:53,859
Prepare for the Almighty’s
judgment,

447
00:19:53,942 --> 00:19:56,737
thou stinking fruit
of rotted vine!

448
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:00,157
(horn playing)

449
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:03,327
Pumpkin segregation forever!

450
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:05,287
(groans)

451
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:06,830
(all sigh)

452
00:20:06,914 --> 00:20:08,582
I can’t live on the outside.

453
00:20:08,665 --> 00:20:10,584
I can’t!

454
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:12,586
(whimpering)

455
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:17,507
Milhouse, your childlike
innocence saved us all!

456
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:19,509
Tom, how can we repay you?

457
00:20:19,593 --> 00:20:21,511
How about
a Thanksgiving feast?

458
00:20:21,595 --> 00:20:22,971
You can carve
the turkey.

459
00:20:23,055 --> 00:20:25,891
(gasps)
You eat turkeys?!

460
00:20:25,974 --> 00:20:27,017
Oh, yeah.

461
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:28,435
It’s delicious!

462
00:20:28,518 --> 00:20:30,062
Especially when
we take stuffing

463
00:20:30,145 --> 00:20:31,647
and shove it up
the turkey’s...

464
00:20:31,730 --> 00:20:34,441
Revenge!

465
00:20:34,524 --> 00:20:36,151
(kids screaming)

466
00:20:39,696 --> 00:20:42,741
Looks like those kids found
the true spirit of Halloween.

467
00:20:42,824 --> 00:20:44,743
Or Thanksgiving.

468
00:20:44,826 --> 00:20:46,370
Or whatever.

469
00:20:46,453 --> 00:20:48,080
And for those of you who feel

470
00:20:48,163 --> 00:20:50,666
like we’ve trampled
on a beloved children’s classic,

471
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:53,460
I encourage you to write
to the following address.

472
00:20:53,543 --> 00:20:54,878
♪ ♪

473
00:20:54,962 --> 00:20:57,547
Happy Holidays, everyone!

